Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?perf=20wave=2020=20patch=200087=20=E2=80=94=20e?=
 =?UTF-8?q?ngine-side=20flip-phase=20instrumentation=20(Lever=20A)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

DOS-PORT (patch 0087, Phase 9 wave 20 Lever A). Per-phase timing
brackets inside `Renderer::flip()` decompose the 16.7 ms wave-18
measured per-flip flush into named buckets so wave-20 analysis can
identify what dominates the unaccounted ~11.6 ms misc slice
(per docs/PHASE9-WAVE-20-COLD-PICKUP.md § 1).

Pairs with patches/SDL/0035 (sdl-engine deliverable) which
instruments the SDL3-DOS flush primitives. Together: SDL/0035 names
the slow-path / fast-path internals; nxengine/0087 names the
engine-visible bucket each flip falls into. Cross-side correlation
in the W20A iter readout identifies misc-slice attribution.

Env gate: SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FLIP_INSTR (strict "1" match per CLAUDE.md
convention; default OFF). Cached once at init via static-const-bool
so the optimizer can hoist the per-flip guard at -O2. When unset the
patch adds:
  - one branch-on-cached-bool per phase site (5 sites)
  - one comparison in _direct_vesa_present (gen-bumps tap)
  - the env-var read at first call (one getenv)
  - sample-array storage (~4 KB static state, never written)
Per the "default OFF means zero added cost" contract requirement.

Phase brackets (inside flip()):
  drain_ns        — SDL_FlushRenderer durations summed across both
                    diff-path and dirty-path drain sites. Only one
                    fires per flip (gated on _renderer_queue_dirty)
                    but we sum defensively.
  dirty_ns        — diff/bbox compute window; subtracts in-window
                    drain time so drain + dirty are non-overlapping
                    buckets.
  present_ns      — duration of the actual flush call. One of three
                    paths fires per flip:
                      SDL_DOSVesaDirectPresentFull (DV path)
                      SDL_UpdateWindowSurfaceRects (partial)
                      SDL_RenderPresent             (full)
                    Each branch bumps its path-mix counter.
  housekeeping_ns — post-present SDL_GetWindowSurface + palette
                    rebind. Sub-ms when DOSKUTSU_CACHE_WINSURF=1
                    short-circuits.
  total_ns        — reuses the existing _flip_inner_dt_ns measurement
                    (SDL_GetTicksNS at flip entry → flip exit).
                    Composed with the other 4 buckets for math:
                    dirty + drain + present + housekeeping ≤ total
                    (residual = engine-tick + audio + misc at outer
                    flip granularity).

Aggregation: every 100 flips, sort 100-element sample arrays once
each (5 × ~700 std::sort comparisons = << 1 ms on PODP83), compute
{min, median, mean, p95, max} in ms (two-decimal), emit 5
[flip-stat ...] lines + 1 [flip-counters ...] line, reset.

Output format (per flush-instr's contract; matches wave-19 DELTA-STAT
shape so the W20A analysis can reuse parsing):

  [flip-stat n=100 phase=drain        min=X.XX med=Y.YY mean=Z.ZZ p95=P.PP max=M.MM ms]
  [flip-stat n=100 phase=dirty        min=X.XX med=Y.YY mean=Z.ZZ p95=P.PP max=M.MM ms]
  [flip-stat n=100 phase=present      min=X.XX med=Y.YY mean=Z.ZZ p95=P.PP max=M.MM ms]
  [flip-stat n=100 phase=housekeeping min=X.XX med=Y.YY mean=Z.ZZ p95=P.PP max=M.MM ms]
  [flip-stat n=100 phase=total        min=X.XX med=Y.YY mean=Z.ZZ p95=P.PP max=M.MM ms]
  [flip-counters present_path_direct_vesa=N present_path_render=N
                 present_path_partial=N gen_bumps=N housekeeping_skipped=N]

Path-mix counters disambiguate which present primitive fired. Per
flush-instr's contract addendum, three of these likely show 100/0/0
in the W20A direct-VESA-default config — that's the confirmation we
need that present_ns is timing the DV path, not a fall-back.

gen_bumps counts mid-run fb_state re-inits ONLY (excludes first-call
init); steady-state should read 0/100. A non-zero value correlates
with sdl-engine's `direct_vesa_lazy_reinit_calls` and signals a mode
change / window re-create / similar event during the block.

housekeeping_skipped counts DOSKUTSU_CACHE_WINSURF=1 ablation hits
per flip. Helps interpret housekeeping_ns distribution: 100/100 means
the cheap path; 0/100 means the expensive SDL_GetWindowSurface +
palette rebind every flip.

Output routes through nxengine LOG_INFO macro → patch 0036
fsync-per-line → DEBUG.LOG (or W20A.LOG when DOSKUTSU_LOG_TAG=W20A
per nxengine/0069). Mid-run grep works on both DOSBox-X and real HW
per memory/sdl3_dos_quirks.md.

docs/BOOT.md: env var documentation belongs to sdl-engine's SDL/0035
patch (single canonical entry; this patch references the shared hint
in its initVideo log line for grep-ability but doesn't double-write
the docs entry per coordination with flush-instr).

Test plan (subsequent task #3 / #4):
  - DOSBox-X smoke (build-qa): visual A/B with FLIP_INSTR off + on;
    LOG line greps for [flip-stat ... phase=...] and [flip-counters ...]
    blocks. Must show 5 stat lines + 1 counter line per 100 flips when
    enabled, zero added log lines when disabled.
  - Real-HW iter W20A (realhw): single PLAY, FLIP_INSTR=1 +
    FORCE_LFB=1 stack (DIRECT_VESA defaults ON post-0088). 3 min title
    + 1 min cmod scene. Logback to /tmp/wave20A/W20A.LOG +
    /tmp/wave20A/W20ASDL.LOG.
  - Analysis (task #5): identify which phase dominates the misc slice
    per phase9_misc_dominates.md framing; advance Lever C/D/E based
    on dominant phase + counter signal.

Reference:
  patches/SDL/0035 (paired SDL-side flush instrumentation)
  patches/nxengine-evo/0086-perf-wave-18-direct-vesa-hotpath.patch
  patches/nxengine-evo/0036-djgpp-fsync-debug-log-per-line.patch
  memory/phase9_misc_dominates.md
  memory/perf_predictions_unreliable.md
  docs/PHASE9-WAVE-20-COLD-PICKUP.md § 3 Lever A

